         <abstract id="aspace_c1c48cb305549fe122046db7fc490d48">Roger Miller was a lecturer and Research Supervisor at the Smith School of Social Work in the late 1950's, until taking a position permanently at Smith as Director of Research in 1960.  In 1967, he took the position of Director of the Program of Advanced study, a position he held until he retired in 1996.  His papers contain Miller's professional papers, including correspondence, committee minutes, brochures, grants, and research evaluations.</abstract>
